# Nodes Base Development

- Read `packages/nodes-base/AGENTS.md` before adding or changing built-in nodes or credentials.
- Choose declarative routing when it fits; use `execute`, `poll`, `trigger`, or `webhook` only when the node type requires custom logic.
- Keep node operation descriptions, fields, and helpers separated following nearby node structure.
- Use clear `displayName`, `description`, sensible defaults, and `displayOptions` for conditional fields.
- Use `NodeOperationError` for user-facing validation failures and `NodeApiError` for API failures.
- Support `continueOnFail` where surrounding nodes do.
- Mock external APIs with `nock` and prefer existing `NodeTestHarness` workflow-test patterns.
